quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  26,91,"And the (Hell) Fire will be placed in full view of the erring."
  26,92,"And it will be said to them: "
  26,93,""
  27,64,"Is not He (better than your so-called gods) Who originates creation, and shall thereafter repeat it, and Who provides for you from heaven and earth? Is there any ilâh (god) with Allâh? Say: "
  27,65,"Say: "
  27,66,"Nay, they have no knowledge of the Hereafter. Nay, they are in doubt about it. Nay, they are in complete blindness about it."
  28,37,"Mûsâ (Moses) said: "
  28,38,"Fir‘aun (Pharaoh) said: "
  28,39,"And he and his hosts were arrogant in the land, without right, and they thought that they would never return to Us."
  29,4,"Or think those who do evil deeds that they can outstrip Us (i.e. escape Our punishment)? Evil is that which they judge!"
  29,5,"Whoever hopes for the Meeting{1} with Allâh, then Allâh’s Term is surely coming and He is the All-Hearer, the All-Knower.",footnotes:1:[{29:5} See (Verse 6:31) and its footnote.]
  29,6,"And whosoever strives, he strives only for himself. Verily, Allâh stands not in need of any of the ‘Âlamîn (mankind, jinn, and all that exists)."